reviews.text: Have lunch with a friend at Chill Cafe today.  There are quite a list of regular set lunch to choose as well as special lunch menu which is different every day.  We tried seafood linguine in lobster sauce and angus beef rib eye.  Both are delicious.  Coffee is also good.  Better book in advance for lunch on weekdays 'cos there are lots of offices around.

It has an indoor and outdoor seating for the smokers. Western lunch or dinner food and lighter snacks on offer. Happy hour was till 8pm. Food was mid sized so will likely order an extra dish to be full. Taste is good and service is good.

This restaurant located at a commercial building. Expected full house during weekdays lunch. On the other hand, if you go to this restaurant during weekends, no need to reserve the table and easily get the seats. So it is good for a small group of friends (2-4 people) gathering over the weekend. 

There are lunch set avalible over weekends. The set includes soup or salad, main dish and a cup of tea / coffee. Average price of a lunch set before the 10% service charge is around HK$130.
The food and price is decent. The atmosphere is pretty good as well
Excellent Service and very tasty food. Love to come here for lunch set
